text.tspan: Friday of the Sacrament of Confirmation
Courage, Skill, Piety, Fear of God

g.inkscape:label: The fruits of the grace of the Holy Spirit

tspan.tspan: Love, Joy, Peace, Patience, Goodness, Kindness,

text.tspan: Visit the circle of souls faithful to You.
Hearts that are the work of your hands.
You are the anointing of our souls,
A living spring, love, heat of fire.
For thou hast strength from the right hand of the Father,
You enrich our language with speech.
Pour holy love into our hearts
And the frail weakness of our bodies
Refresh with the constancy of your strength.
Let him follow your conductor on the way
We will pass evil, which tempts us.
Let us know the Father through you,
Let the Son also be known.
And you, one breath of two,
Let us confess with all our strength.
Let God be glory to God,
And to him who comforts us,
Let the tribute of the eternal glories flow.

g.inkscape:label: Come, Holy Spirit (Sequence to the Holy Spirit)

text.tspan: Let down from the heavens taken
You will cool down at work
In the heat of living water
Heal the wound of the heart
Give me the merit of bravery
Give me the merit of bravery
